away. I&nbsp;automatically looked at&nbsp;the&nbsp;ledge. Don Genaro was&nbsp;there&nbsp;again. That&nbsp;did not&nbsp;interest&nbsp;me. I&nbsp;<br>noticed&nbsp;semiconsciously&nbsp;that&nbsp;it&nbsp;was&nbsp;very&nbsp;difficult&nbsp;for&nbsp;me&nbsp;to&nbsp;breathe,&nbsp;but&nbsp;before&nbsp;I&nbsp;could&nbsp;have&nbsp;a&nbsp;<br>thought&nbsp;about&nbsp;it,&nbsp;don&nbsp;Genaro&nbsp;jumped&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;ground.&nbsp;That&nbsp;act&nbsp;did&nbsp;not&nbsp;catch&nbsp;my&nbsp;interest&nbsp;either.&nbsp;He&nbsp;<br>came&nbsp;over&nbsp;to&nbsp;me&nbsp;and&nbsp;helped&nbsp;me&nbsp;stand&nbsp;up,&nbsp;holding&nbsp;me&nbsp;by&nbsp;the&nbsp;arm;&nbsp;don&nbsp;Juan&nbsp;held&nbsp;my&nbsp;other&nbsp;arm.&nbsp;<br>They&nbsp;propped&nbsp;me&nbsp;up&nbsp;between&nbsp;the&nbsp;two&nbsp;of&nbsp;them.&nbsp;Then&nbsp;it&nbsp;was&nbsp;only&nbsp;don&nbsp;Genaro&nbsp;who&nbsp;was&nbsp;helping&nbsp;me&nbsp;<br>walk.&nbsp;He&nbsp;whispered&nbsp;something&nbsp;in&nbsp;my&nbsp;ear&nbsp;that&nbsp;I&nbsp;could&nbsp;not&nbsp;understand&nbsp;and&nbsp;suddenly&nbsp;I&nbsp;felt&nbsp;that&nbsp;he&nbsp;<br>had&nbsp;pulled&nbsp;my&nbsp;body&nbsp;in&nbsp;some&nbsp;strange&nbsp;way;&nbsp;he&nbsp;grabbed&nbsp;me,&nbsp;in&nbsp;a&nbsp;manner&nbsp;of&nbsp;speaking,&nbsp;by&nbsp;the&nbsp;skin&nbsp;of&nbsp;<br>my&nbsp;stomach&nbsp;and&nbsp;pulled&nbsp;me&nbsp;up&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;ledge,&nbsp;or&nbsp;perhaps&nbsp;onto&nbsp;another&nbsp;rock.&nbsp;I&nbsp;knew&nbsp;that&nbsp;for&nbsp;an&nbsp;<br>instant&nbsp;I&nbsp;was&nbsp;on&nbsp;a&nbsp;rock.&nbsp;I&nbsp;could&nbsp;have&nbsp;sworn&nbsp;that&nbsp;it&nbsp;was&nbsp;the&nbsp;rock&nbsp;ledge;&nbsp;the&nbsp;image&nbsp;was&nbsp;so&nbsp;fleeting,&nbsp;<br>however,&nbsp;that&nbsp;I&nbsp;could&nbsp;not&nbsp;evaluate&nbsp;it&nbsp;in&nbsp;detail.&nbsp;Then&nbsp;I&nbsp;felt&nbsp;that&nbsp;something&nbsp;in&nbsp;me&nbsp;faltered&nbsp;and&nbsp;I&nbsp;fell&nbsp;<br>backwards.&nbsp;I&nbsp;had&nbsp;a&nbsp;faint&nbsp;feeling&nbsp;of&nbsp;anguish&nbsp;or&nbsp;perhaps