&quot;What&nbsp;was&nbsp;going&nbsp;to&nbsp;be&nbsp;revealed&nbsp;to&nbsp;you&nbsp;was&nbsp;your&nbsp;death,&quot;&nbsp;don&nbsp;Juan&nbsp;said.&nbsp;&quot;That's&nbsp;the&nbsp;danger&nbsp;of&nbsp;<br>
indulging.&nbsp;Especially&nbsp;for&nbsp;you,&nbsp;since&nbsp;you&nbsp;are&nbsp;naturally&nbsp;so&nbsp;exaggerated.&nbsp;Your&nbsp;<i>tonal&nbsp;</i>is&nbsp;so&nbsp;given&nbsp;to&nbsp;<br>indulging that&nbsp;it&nbsp;threatens&nbsp;the&nbsp;totality of&nbsp;you. This&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;terrible&nbsp;way of&nbsp;being.&quot;<br>
&quot;What&nbsp;can I&nbsp;do?&quot;<br>&quot;Your&nbsp;<i>tonal&nbsp;</i>has&nbsp;to be&nbsp;convinced with reasons, your&nbsp;<i>nagual&nbsp;</i>with actions, until&nbsp;one&nbsp;props&nbsp;the&nbsp;<br>
other. As&nbsp;I&nbsp;have&nbsp;told you, the&nbsp;<i>tonal&nbsp;</i>rules, and yet&nbsp;it&nbsp;is&nbsp;very vulnerable. The&nbsp;<i>nagual,&nbsp;</i>on the&nbsp;other&nbsp;<br>hand, never, or&nbsp;almost&nbsp;never, acts&nbsp;out;&nbsp;but&nbsp;when it&nbsp;does, it&nbsp;terrifies&nbsp;the&nbsp;<i>tonal.</i><br>
&quot;This&nbsp;morning&nbsp;your&nbsp;<i>tonal&nbsp;</i>got&nbsp;frightened&nbsp;and&nbsp;began&nbsp;to&nbsp;shrink&nbsp;by&nbsp;itself,&nbsp;and&nbsp;then&nbsp;your&nbsp;<i>nagual&nbsp;</i><br>
