I'm&nbsp;going&nbsp;to&nbsp;tell&nbsp;you&nbsp;the&nbsp;story&nbsp;of&nbsp;a&nbsp;band&nbsp;of&nbsp;warriors&nbsp;who&nbsp;lived&nbsp;in&nbsp;another&nbsp;time&nbsp;on&nbsp;the&nbsp;mountains,&nbsp;<br>somewhere&nbsp;in that&nbsp;direction.&quot;<br>
He&nbsp;casually&nbsp;pointed&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;east,&nbsp;but&nbsp;then,&nbsp;after&nbsp;a&nbsp;moment's&nbsp;hesitation,&nbsp;he&nbsp;seemed&nbsp;to&nbsp;change&nbsp;his&nbsp;<br>
mind and stood up and pointed to the&nbsp;distant&nbsp;northern mountains.<br>
&quot;No. They lived in that&nbsp;direction,&quot;&nbsp;he&nbsp;said, looking at&nbsp;me&nbsp;and smiling with an air&nbsp;of&nbsp;erudition.&nbsp;<br>
&quot;Exactly one&nbsp;hundred and thirty-five&nbsp;kilometers&nbsp;from&nbsp;here.&quot;<br>
Don&nbsp;Genaro&nbsp;was&nbsp;perhaps&nbsp;imitating&nbsp;me.&nbsp;His&nbsp;mouth&nbsp;and&nbsp;forehead&nbsp;were&nbsp;contracted,&nbsp;his&nbsp;hands&nbsp;<br>
