Don Genaro paused;&nbsp;Pablito assented to his&nbsp;words&nbsp;by nodding.<br>&quot;If&nbsp;you&nbsp;two&nbsp;decide&nbsp;to&nbsp;return&nbsp;to&nbsp;this&nbsp;earth,&quot;&nbsp;he&nbsp;said,&nbsp;&quot;you&nbsp;will&nbsp;have&nbsp;to&nbsp;wait&nbsp;like&nbsp;true&nbsp;warriors&nbsp;<br>
until&nbsp;your&nbsp;tasks&nbsp;are&nbsp;fulfilled.&nbsp;That&nbsp;waiting&nbsp;is&nbsp;very&nbsp;much&nbsp;like&nbsp;the&nbsp;walk&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;warrior&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;story.&nbsp;<br>You&nbsp;see,&nbsp;the&nbsp;warrior&nbsp;had&nbsp;run&nbsp;out&nbsp;of&nbsp;human&nbsp;time&nbsp;and&nbsp;so&nbsp;have&nbsp;you.&nbsp;The&nbsp;only&nbsp;difference&nbsp;is&nbsp;in&nbsp;who&nbsp;is&nbsp;<br>aiming&nbsp;at&nbsp;you.&nbsp;Those&nbsp;who&nbsp;were&nbsp;aiming&nbsp;at&nbsp;the&nbsp;warrior&nbsp;were&nbsp;his&nbsp;warrior&nbsp;comrades.&nbsp;But&nbsp;what's&nbsp;<br>aiming&nbsp;at&nbsp;you&nbsp;two&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;unknown.&nbsp;Your&nbsp;only&nbsp;chance&nbsp;is&nbsp;your&nbsp;impeccability.&nbsp;You&nbsp;must&nbsp;wait&nbsp;<br>without&nbsp;looking&nbsp;back.&nbsp;You&nbsp;must&nbsp;wait&nbsp;without&nbsp;expecting&nbsp;rewards.&nbsp;And&nbsp;you&nbsp;must&nbsp;aim&nbsp;all&nbsp;of&nbsp;your&nbsp;<br>personal&nbsp;<i>power&nbsp;</i>at&nbsp;fulfilling your&nbsp;tasks.<br>
