I&nbsp;experienced a&nbsp;shock in my stomach. Pablito began to shiver&nbsp;quietly.<br>&quot;A&nbsp;warrior&nbsp;must&nbsp;be&nbsp;always&nbsp;ready,&quot;&nbsp;he&nbsp;said.&nbsp;&quot;The&nbsp;fate&nbsp;of&nbsp;all&nbsp;of&nbsp;us&nbsp;here&nbsp;has&nbsp;been&nbsp;to&nbsp;know&nbsp;that&nbsp;<br>
we&nbsp;are&nbsp;the&nbsp;prisoners&nbsp;of&nbsp;<i>power</i>. No one&nbsp;knows&nbsp;why us&nbsp;in particular, but&nbsp;what&nbsp;a&nbsp;great&nbsp;fortune!&quot;<br>
Don&nbsp;Genaro&nbsp;stopped&nbsp;talking&nbsp;and&nbsp;lowered&nbsp;his&nbsp;head&nbsp;as&nbsp;if&nbsp;he&nbsp;were&nbsp;exhausted.&nbsp;That&nbsp;had&nbsp;been&nbsp;the&nbsp;<br>
first&nbsp;time&nbsp;that&nbsp;I&nbsp;had heard him&nbsp;speak in such terms.<br>
&quot;It&nbsp;is&nbsp;mandatory&nbsp;here&nbsp;that&nbsp;a&nbsp;warrior&nbsp;says&nbsp;good-by&nbsp;to&nbsp;all&nbsp;those&nbsp;present&nbsp;and&nbsp;to&nbsp;all&nbsp;those&nbsp;he&nbsp;leaves&nbsp;<br>
